HEADWORD: Receptive
<hw>Re*cep"tive</hw> <pr>(r⟦esl⟧*s⟦ecr⟧p"t⟦icr⟧v)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>r⟦eacute⟧ceptif</ets>. See <er>Receive</er>.]</ety>
<def>Having the quality of receiving; able or inclined to take in,
absorb, hold, or contain; receiving or containing; <as>as, a
<ex>receptive</ex> mind</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Imaginary space is <qex>receptive</qex> of all bodies.</q>
<rj><qau>Glanvill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Receptiveness</ent>⟦br⟧
